.SH NAME
dotty-tmux - Tmux sessions for agent-driven development.


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBdotty tmux  [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Start and attach tmux dev sessions laid out for coding agents: an editor
window with a small shell split, one window per installed agent (opencode,
codex, claude), and a shell window, all named after the repository.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for tmux


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--profile\fP=""
	profile to operate on (defaults to the active profile)


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  dotty tmux new
  dotty tmux new dotty
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBdotty(1)\fP, \fBdotty-tmux-new(1)\fP
